  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <meta name="theme-color" content="#ffffff" />
  <meta name="description" content="A design system for the Fifth World." />
</head>
<body class="thefifthworld">
<header>
  <nav class="personal">
    <ul>
      <li><a href="standard-loggedin.html">Log in</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">How to Join</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>
  <h1 class="logo">
    <a href="/">
      <img src="https://thefifthworld.s3.us-east-2.stackpathstorage.com/design/img/wordmark.black.svg" alt="The Fifth World" />
    </a>
  </h1>
</header>
<main>
  <form action="/member" method="POST">
    <input type="hidden" name="id" value="<%= member.id %>" />
    <label for="name">Name</label>
    <input type="text" id="name" name="name" value="<%= member.name %>" placeholder="What would you like us to call you?" />
    <label for="email">Email</label>
    <input type="email" id="email" name="email" value="<%= member.email %>" placeholder="you@example.com" />
    <aside>
      <p>A long, memorable phrase, like a sentence, can provide more security than an arcane string of random letters and numbers that you’ll have a hard time remembering. That’s why we ask for a pass phrase. We also leave it open in plain text to make it easier for you to come up with and use a stronger one. You can probably check for someone looking over your shoulder more easily than you can check for hackers.</p>
      <p>If you submit this form without providing anything here, your old pass phrase will remain unchanged.</p>
      <label for="passphrase">Passphrase</label>
      <input type="text" id="passphrase" name="passphrase" placeholder="Enter a secret passphrase" />
    </aside>
    <label for="bio">About</label>
    <textarea id="bio" name="bio"><%= member.bio %></textarea>
    <h2>Links</h2>
    <p>If you&rsquo;d like to make it easier for other people to find and follow you on social media or other networks, provide some links here. We&rsquo;ll show any that you provide on your profile. Any you choose not to share will simply not appear.</p>
    <label for="facebook">Facebook</label>
    <input type="url" id="facebook" name="facebook" value="<%= member.links.facebook %>" placeholder="https://facebook.com/your-username-here" />
    <label for="twitter">Twitter</label>
    <input type="url" id="twitter" name="twitter" value="<%= member.links.twitter %>" placeholder="https://twitter.com/your-username-here" />
    <label for="github">GitHub</label>
    <input type="url" id="github" name="github" value="<%= member.links.github %>" placeholder="https://github.com/your-username-here" />
    <label for="patreon">Patreon</label>
    <input type="url" id="patreon" name="patreon" value="<%= member.links.patreon %>" placeholder="https://patreon.com/your-username-here" />
    <label for="website">Website</label>
    <input type="url" id="website" name="website" value="<%= member.links.website %>" placeholder="https://yourwebsite.com" />
    <p class="buttons">
      <button>Save</button>
      <a href="/member/<%= member.id %>" class="btn secondary">Cancel</a>
    </p>
  </form>
</main>
<nav class="site">
  <ul>
    <li class="explore"><a href="/explore">Explore</a></li>
    <li class="hear"><a href="/stories">Hear</a></li>
    <li class="see"><a href="/art">See</a></li>
    <li class="play"><a href="/play">Play</a></li>
  </ul>
</nav>
